Your domain name should be pointed to your server before running ceymail.
You may have to contact your Server provider to lift email sending limitations.


Instructions
------------
$ chmod +x install.sh ceymail.sh
$ ./install.sh
$ ceymail

1. Install & Configure CeyMail.
2. Add a domain & email account.
3. Login to your account.

* CD into /etc/letsencrypt/live
* Copy fullchain.pem and privkey.pem into /etc/letsencrypt/live/mail/.
* Make sure your server's firewall allows all the ports used by CeyMail. (80, 443, 25, 465, 587, 993, 143, 110, 995)


DNS Records
------------

MX
Priority	Host 			Target
10			 @		$domain

SPF
Host	 	Target
 @		v=spf1 +a +mx ip4:1.2.3.4 ~all

DMARC
	 Host	 				Value
_dmarc.$domain		v=DMARC1; p=quarantine; pct=100;


DKIM
You can find your DKIM key at ~/ceymail/DKIM_Record.txt

With the DKIM Record, remove white spaces, double quotes and brackets at the ends.
Add a TXT record for DKIM with an example like this
THIS IS JUST AN EXAMPLE.

	Host 				Value
mail._domainkey  v=DKIM1; h=sha256; k=rsa; p=MIIBIjANBgkqhkasd9B
